        reason: 'The Julian value of 365.25 days exceeds the true tropical year (~365.2422 days) by about 11 minutes, accumulating roughly 10 days of error by the 16th century and drifting the equinox away from its Nicene date. Pope Gregory XIII\'s bull Inter gravissimas decrees the correction: ten days are dropped (4 October 1582 is followed by 15 October), and the leap rule is amended to make the mean year 365.2425 days, superseding Caesar\'s figure.',
