        reason: 'Hubble\'s paper "Cepheid Variables in Spiral Nebulae" is read in absentia by Henry Norris Russell at the joint AAS/AAAS meeting in Washington, D.C. on January 1, 1925, and shares the AAAS $1,000 prize. The Cepheid distance places M31 far outside the Milky Way, settling the 1920 Shapley–Curtis "Great Debate" decisively in favor of external "island universe" galaxies.',
