    text: 'The St. Bartholomew\'s Day Massacre began in Paris before dawn on 24 August 1572, when Catholic forces killed the Huguenot leader Admiral Gaspard de Coligny and thousands of Protestants gathered for the royal wedding of Margaret of Valois and Henry of Navarre; the killing spread to provincial cities over the following weeks.',
