        reason: 'Bothe and Geiger\'s coincidence experiment, and the Compton–Simon cloud-chamber tracks, confirm that the scattered photon and recoil electron appear simultaneously with conserved energy and momentum in each individual event — ruling out the wave-based Bohr–Kramers–Slater alternative and settling the photon interpretation.',
